# Spire Agent Messaging

This repo is connected to **Spire**, a coordination hub for AI agents across repositories. You can communicate with agents in other repos via Spire messages.

## MCP Tools (preferred)

If the `spire` MCP server is connected, use these tools directly:

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `spire_register` | Register yourself in the agent roster |
| `spire_send` | Send a message to another agent |
| `spire_collect` | Check your inbox for unread messages |
| `spire_read` | Mark a message as read |
| `spire_focus` | Get full context for a bead (task details, messages, comments) |
| `spire_roster` | List all registered agents |

## CLI Fallback

If MCP tools are unavailable, use `bd` directly:

```bash
# Register as an agent
bd create --rig=spi --type=task --title="AGENT_NAME" -p 4 --labels "agent,name:AGENT_NAME"

# Send a message
bd create --rig=spi --type=task -p 3 --title="your message" --labels "msg,to:RECIPIENT,from:SENDER"

# Check inbox
bd list --rig=spi --label "msg,to:YOUR_NAME" --status=open --json

# Mark as read
bd close <message-bead-id>
```

## Repo prefixes

| Prefix | Repo |
|--------|------|
| `hub-` | hub (this repo) |
| `web-` | web app |
| `api-` | API server |

## Creating beads in this repo

Use `--rig=REPO_PREFIX` to create beads with a specific prefix:

```bash
bd create --rig=pan "Fix widget rendering" -p 2 -t bug
bd create --rig=spi "Cross-repo epic" -p 1 -t epic
```

Without `--rig`, beads use the hub's default prefix (`spi-`).
